text: Had our dinner at this restaurant. A chinese muslim restaurant selling variety of mee tarik and stir fried meal. We ordered beef noodles, chinese hamburger and egg fried rice with kopi tarik and ice lemon tea. The food were good, for me i like it spicy (you can request to the waitress). The price also reasonable and the place itself was has a nice vibes.

Best Muslim chinese Restaurant halal of my entire life
Excellent service and tasty food !

I thoroughly enjoy the Chinese spicy taste. The steamed dumplings are delicious, and the cucumber salad and spicy stir-fried chicken taste like Korean fried chicken. The spicy stir-fried potatoes ordered by my daughter's friend were the most delicious. Crispy on the outside and fluffy on the inside, it feels like a Chinese-style potato wedge. Spicy and crispy foamy potatoes are a taste that makes you want to eat them again. I automatically think of beer.
The food is delicious and big portions
